history.content:
Are you interested in technology, consulting, product management, design, or all of the above? DiversaTech is the premier student-run tech consulting organization at UC Berkeley, where we form interdisciplinary teams of students to deliver innovative and practical recommendations for our clients, ranging from startups like Affirm and Jumpstart, to bigger tech companies such as Google and LinkedIn. We accept people of all majors and strongly encourage underrepresented minorities and transfer students to apply! No prior technical or consulting experience is required.

🎉Apply here: diversatech.org/apply 🎉 Deadline: Friday, February 5th, 11AM PST

Coffee Chats Get to know our consultants, project managers, executives, and senior advisors in 15-minute coffee chats! Time slots run from Saturday, January 30th thru Sunday, January 31st. Sign up for a time slot at https://tinyurl.com/Sp21dtcoffeechats.

Infosession 1 We will present our team and the consulting projects lined up for this semester, followed by a networking session. Tuesday, February 2nd, 8PM – 10PM PST

Zoom link: berkeley.zoom.us/my/diversatech

Infosession 2 If you were unable to attend the first infosession, no worries! Join us at our second infosession on Thursday for the same experience. Thursday, February 4th, 8PM – 10PM PST Zoom link: berkeley.zoom.us/my/diversatech

Hope to see you there!
